djtdon - Xvid and DivX are SUPPOSED to be small so that (a) they download fast, and (b) they fit on a CD (rather than a DVD5/DVD9). If you want better quality then you should perhaps be looking for DVD5/DVD9 downloads - and then put up with downloads which take six times as long (or more)!

Hint... small files = loss of quality, large files = best quality. Your choice.
